Class Final_Project

  • java.lang.Object
    • Final_Project

  • public class Final_Project
extends java.lang.Object

    CSCI 1105 Final Project

    In this program, the user inputs a string of RNA nucleotide bases and the program returns the original codon sequence, a randomly mutated codon sequence, and then prints each corresponding amino acid sequence. Also prints total codons, number of point mutations, and amino acids changes.

    Created: 5-6-19

    Author:
    Renee Linford

      • toCodon

        public static java.lang.String[] toCodon(java.lang.String[] baseSequence)
        This method is used to concat strings in an array. Method concats 3 indicies at a time (i.e., array with index values of "A A A A A A" becomes "AAA AAA"). Best for changing a string array of RNA characters to an array of codons. 
        Examples: 
 	toCodon(baseSequence[]) returns codonSequence[]
        Parameters:
        baseSequence - (String []; an array of strings where each index is one character such as A, C, G, or U)
        Returns:
        codonSequence (String []; an array of strings where each index is three characters such as AAA)

      • toAminoAcid

        public static java.lang.String[] toAminoAcid(java.lang.String[] codonSeq)
        This method is used to change an array of codons to an array of amino acids. Each index of the codon array is matched to its corresponding amino acid, and that amino acid is copied to a new array. Strings should be in uppercase. 
        Example:
 	toAminoAcid(codonSequence[]) returns aminoAcidSequence[]
        Parameters:
        codonSeq - (String []; a string array where each index is three characters long, such as AAA or UGC.)
        Returns:
        aaSeq (String []; a string array where each index is a string representing an amino acid, such as LYS for the codon AAA, or CYS for the codon UGC.)

      • mutate

        public static java.lang.String[] mutate(java.lang.String[] sequence)
        This method takes a string array containing indices of single characters (A, C, G, or U), and randomly selects a random number of indices to change. It will change the index character to a randomly selected A, C, G or U character. Returns mutated array containgin indices of single characters (A, C, G, or U). 
        Example:
	mutate(sequence[]) returns mutatedSequence[]
        Parameters:
        sequence - (String []; a string array of single base characters to be randomly altered.)
        Returns:
        mutatedSeq (String []; a string array of single base characters with indices randomly changed.)
